Get the position numbers of the coefficients

Source: R/coefficient-positions.R
get_coef_positions.Rd

Get the position numbers of the coefficients

Usage

get_coef_positions(x)

Arguments

x

A logistic regression model.

Value

Positions of each coefficient.

Examples

get_coef_positions(lr_caused)
#>                    Coefficients Position
#> (Intercept)          -0.3511784        1
#> jur_race_wBlack       0.4685659        2
#> jur_race_wHispanic    0.5768085        3
#> jur_race_wAsian       0.4404095        4
#> jur_race_wOther       0.2393870        5
get_coef_positions(lr_cause_inn)
#>                              Coefficients Position
#> (Intercept)                   -3.31620417        1
#> i_30North                     -0.35123495        2
#> i_30Split                     -0.61562146        3
#> jur_race_wBlack               -1.20829811        4
#> jur_race_wHispanic            -0.76977214        5
#> jur_race_wAsian              -14.24986432        6
#> jur_race_wOther               -0.06818609        7
#> i_30North:jur_race_wBlack      1.74024302        8
#> i_30Split:jur_race_wBlack    -12.42594474        9
#> i_30North:jur_race_wHispanic   1.36915833       10
#> i_30Split:jur_race_wHispanic -12.86447071       11
#> i_30North:jur_race_wAsian     14.80824249       12
#> i_30Split:jur_race_wAsian      0.61562147       13
#> i_30North:jur_race_wOther      0.89404362       14
#> i_30Split:jur_race_wOther    -13.56605676       15
